# picomatch 4.0.3 in npm's internal glob — not reachable from user input.
# npm@latest ships with this version; no fix available without downgrading npm.
# Will be resolved when npm releases a version with picomatch >=4.0.4.
CVE-2026-33671

# opentelemetry-go: kenv PATH hijack (BSD-only).
# CVE-2026-39883 affects go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.40.0, pulled in
# transitively by Caddy's builder via the custom plugin graph. The vulnerable
# code path only fires on FreeBSD/NetBSD where it invokes the `kenv` command
# without an absolute path. Our runtime image is Alpine Linux — `kenv` does
# not exist and the code path is never taken, so this is not exploitable in
# our deployment. Will be removed once upstream Caddy pulls otel >= 1.43.0.
CVE-2026-39883
